Company Overview of HSBC USA Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
HSBC USA Inc., together with its subsidiaries, provides consumer and commercial banking products, and related financial services in the United States. Its Retail Banking and Wealth Management segment provides deposit taking and account services; residential mortgages, home equity lines of credit, and credit cards; and advisory and wealth management services; and branch services primarily through direct channels, including the contact center, Internet banking, and mobile. The company’s Commercial Banking segment provides global liquidity and cash management, global trade and receivables finance, lending and transaction management, investment banking, and global markets services through commer...
HSBC USA Inc., together with its subsidiaries, provides consumer and commercial banking products, and related financial services in the United States. Its Retail Banking and Wealth Management segment provides deposit taking and account services; residential mortgages, home equity lines of credit, and credit cards; and advisory and wealth management services; and branch services primarily through direct channels, including the contact center, Internet banking, and mobile. The company’s Commercial Banking segment provides global liquidity and cash management, global trade and receivables finance, lending and transaction management, investment banking, and global markets services through commercial centers and retail branch network, as well as through on-line banking channel HSBCnet. Its Global Banking and Markets segment offers loans, working capital, trade, payment and cash management, leveraged and acquisition finance, project and infrastructure finance, asset finance, and mergers and acquisitions advisory services, as well as capital raising services in the debt and equity capital markets for corporate and institutional clients. This segment also provides services in credits and rates, foreign exchanges, precious metals trading, equities, and securities services. The company’s Private Banking segment offers various products and services, including banking, liquidity management, investment services, custody, tailored lending, trust and fiduciary services, insurance, family wealth, and philanthropy advisory services, as well as credit cards and investment banking services. As of December, 31, 2016, it operated 145 branches in New York, 35 in California, 17 in Florida, 9 in New Jersey, 7 in Virginia, 4 in Washington, 3 in Connecticut, 3 in Maryland, 2 in the District of Columbia, 2 in Pennsylvania, and 1 in Delaware. The company was founded in 1850 and is based in New York, New York. HSBC USA Inc. is a subsidiary of HSBC North America Holdings Inc.
Detailed Description


